2026-07-22T14:55Z HDMX-coding-agent created after fixing test_parameterize_works_paths (0289 gate)

--- body ---
## Context

`test_parameterize_works_paths.py::test_dry_run_uses_custom_input` launched a
script subprocess with `cwd=tmp_path` and no `source_root_env()`, so
`import openalex_corpus` only resolved through a leftover wheel in the shared
primary venv — a fresh worktree venv exposed the failure (0289 make check
gate, fixed inline on that branch). Rule 0253 says source roots are never
assumed ambient; other test files launch subprocesses without
`source_root_env()` and may carry the same latent defect, masked the same
way. The defect class needs: subprocess runs a `scripts/*.py` with cwd away
from the repo root, and the script transitively imports `openalex_corpus`.

## Relevant files

- `tests/_source_roots.py` — the helper subprocess launches must use
- `tests/test_io_discipline.py`, `tests/test_pipeline_e2e.py`,
  `tests/test_bias_flag.py`, and ~25 other files with `subprocess.run`
  and no `source_root_env` import

## Actions

1. Enumerate test subprocess launches of `scripts/*.py`; classify by cwd and
   env handling.
2. Pass `env=source_root_env()` where missing; leave non-Python launches
   (ruff, make, git hooks) alone.
3. Consider an adherence guard: a grep test failing on
   `subprocess.run([PYTHON, .*scripts` without `source_root_env` in the
   same file.

## Test

- Run the touched integration tests from a venv without the openalex-corpus
  wheel (any fresh worktree env) — they must pass.

## Verification

- [ ] Touched tests green in a fresh worktree venv

## Invariants

- No test semantics change; only subprocess env plumbing.

## Exit criteria

- [ ] No test subprocess relies on ambient PYTHONPATH or a leftover wheel
